caption.text:
Videogames are a source of tension in many families. Parents are worried about safety, their kids getting obsessed, and are often unsure of the best way to guide their children. My advice, step 1, is play a video game with your child. It’s a great way to share their interest (and that’s always a good thing!), you will see first-hand the content your child is engaging with in the games they play, how they play with their friends online, and where the safety issues are. That way you can make an informed decision in guiding your child.

Looky here, I made another universe, this time my beloved video games fan expression.

I called this title "Retrodown 9158". Why is it call that? Because title is like back to the retro down around in 1985, (the number swap out in a title) there were so many good games happened in 3rd generations console like NES and arcade cabinets.

There are 2 protagonists and 1 minor character for now on start from left to right:
- Meet Knuckle Sandwich! He's a typical fighter class player who really wants to become the best player in the whole arcade! His main weapon is giant hockey gauntlet!
- Meet Scorch Torch! She's a barbarian wielding a fiery heavy sword to roast the enemy all around her. She's one of Big's closest friend
- And lastly, Meet Scrappy Bolt! She's one of their ingenious classmate who likes to bring her lovely rifle with melting scraps as her ammo. Also, she likes to build any her invention such as mech or sentry buddy.

Recently I've been playing AI: The Somnium Files & let me tell you, if you're looking for an intriguing adventure game with mystery and compelling characters, look no further! All the characters are so interesting and leave you wanting to know more about them
I'm about 9 hours in and all of my theories so far have been proven wrong, and the twists have already begun! I'd love to try solving the mystery as the game goes on, but for now I'll just be along for the ride😂

Written by Kotaro Uchikoshi of Zero Escape and the Infinity series; character designs by Yusuke Kozaki from Fire Emblem and No More Heroes fame; with music composed by Keisuke Ito from the Pokemon Mystery Dungeon Series

Play as Kaname Date as he searches for an elusive serial killer, with the assistance of his AI eyeball Aiba, in the secret police department known as ABIS. 🔍 Investigate important locations and search for clues with Aiba's assistance & enter the dreams of persons of interest to gather more information! 
CHECK OUT THIS GAME!! If you love mysterious stories, sci-fi, intriguing characters and fun gameplay, I'm sure you won't be disappointed! It's available on PS4, Nintendo Switch, and Steam🎮

caption.text: Today’s the last day in Amsterdam. Unfortunately. But even though the weather was shit - we really enjoyed our time here as much as we could. It was rainy but we had a shiny mood & these past days were rememberable ones and when I’m looking at the pictures we took of ourselves then the most remarkable thing about them is the fact that happiness makes us more beautiful. It’s sad that everyone of us is forgetting that the most important thing is to be happy and that happiness can be found much easier than we think actually. I just needed this weekend to recall this on my own. Thank you, @kvnpendragon ❤️

caption.text:
Another week another Maker Race challenge, but, not just any challenge  the FINAL one!
-
If it were up to us, we would've loved to keep going as originally planned, however, after the disappointing behaviour shown by many contestants, the weekly eliminations were plentiful and had nothing to do with the course quality anymore.
-
It's sad, but that's people for ya these days. Originally we wanted to pull the plug last weekend, but, we do have some excellent Makers still in the running. Makers who, despite having busy lives themselves, show what a true Champion's dedication is.
-
For them, we're having this final challenge, so everyone can end this on a much more fun level than we nearly ended on. In light of the challenge, the Makers have two weeks to turn a pumpkin into a carriage! 🎃
-
So we're wishing our final contestants luck in proving once and for all who the Maker Champion is -at least to us- 😁
-

"Comodidad en mi desorden"
Al principio crei que era una completa basura, debia entregarlo rapido y queria trabajar en un soporte de tela, pero con el tiempo al cuello tuve que ultilizar lo que mas rapido encontré, carton.
Cuando lo terminé, el acrílico no se secaba y encima se resbalaba, intente arreglarlo pero cada vez empeoraba mas. Lo dejé así, lo entregué así. 
Me rehusaba a aceptar que ese desastre era mío y de mala gana se lo mostré a mi profesora, ella dijo que la idea de la imagen (la cual habia ultilizado para hacer esta "obra") era mostrar lo íntimo, entre uno y uno, las cosas tiradas arriba de la mesa así nomas, los paquetes de pizzas de hace días aun ahí arriba, el videojuego que nos entretiene, todo era parte e iba en conjunto con el carton como soporte, porque el carton aumentaba aun mas la forma del desorden. 
La idea del desorden siempre esta dentro de los parametros de nuestro orden, siempre esta ahi para desorganizar un poco y darse cuenta que uno está dejándose llevar, el desorden nos da orden. No obstante el orden a veces da placer, pero ¿porqué el desorden tampoco lo daría? No le teman a creer en el desorden como orden descomunal de lo monótono, obras en tela hay demasiadas pero pocas en cartón que se apeguen tanto a la idea.
.
.
. 
No me pregunten que carajo quise decir. .
.

preview_comments.text: Sehr schönes Bild! 😍 Ich bin recht scheu und zurückhaltend wenn ich auf neue Menschen treffe. 1. weil ich vom Wesen so bin und 2. um mir einen Eindruck vom Gegenüber zu machen. Ich liege oft richtig mit meiner Einschätzung, aber manchmal wird man auch überrascht ☺️

Ich glaube Menschenkenntnis ist bei mir groß vorhanden aber ich muss auch gefühlt immer wieder sagen Leute nicht voreilig irgendwas denken, oft gibt es Gründe fürs handeln und denken anderer... erstmal abchecken und dann urteilen, oder vllt sogar helfen und und ach das kann man weit fächern :)

caption.text:
★𝕄𝕠𝕟𝕕𝕒𝕪 𝕚𝕤 𝕟𝕠𝕥 𝕞𝕪 𝔻𝕒𝕪 ★
[𝘢𝘥𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘵𝘪𝘴𝘪𝘯𝘨]
•
Moin aus der Tagesklinik . Eine neue (aber Gottseidank kürzere) Woche hat angefangen &’ ich Sitz hier schon und bin die erste die da ist 😂👌🏻 War schon auf der Arbeit so . Ich muss immer wenigstens ne halbe Stunde vor allen anderen da sein ,dann bereite ich alles vor damit der Tag über leichter für meine Kollegen und mich war . So hat man sich auch Zeit gespart . Letztendlich ist das aber meine eigene Entscheidung und ich finde man sollte andere dafür reicht verurteilen wenn diese erst pünktlich kommen . Nicht nur,dass es deren gutes Recht ist ,man sollte sich nicht immer einmischen
•
Ich finde das gilt auch für hier . Ich bemerke das aber auch hin und wieder an mir,dass ich mir meine ein Urteil vorschnell zu erlauben,ohne die Hintergründe zu kennen . Aber oftmals ist es so das ich mit meinem Bauchgefühl richtig liege &’ die Person genauso ist wie ich dachte . Manchmal weiß ich aber nicht ob das ein Fluch oder Segen sein kann . Wie seht Ihr das ? Habt Ihr eine gute Menschenkenntnis ? Passiert es Euch auch mal das Ihr Leute vorschnell verurteilt ? Fehler passieren,wichtig ist,diese zu erkennen und sich zu entschuldigen (auch bei sich selbst)
•
In dem Sinne einen ruhigen Montagmorgen 🙌🏻

#Pokemon #pokemongo #nintendo #pikachu #anime #art #pokedex #pokemoncards #mon #pokemoncommunity #pokemonart #shinypokemon #pokemontrainer #gamefreak #niantic #nintendoswitch #charizard #gamer #manga #gaming #videogames #cosplay #cute #mewtwo #pokemons #ashketchum #pkmn #kawaii #japan #pokemonmaster

De la mano de TDK tenemos The Haunted Mansion ó  La Mansión Encantada. Está basado en una atracción de Disney de la cual también hay una película (con Eddie Murphy). A diferencia de la película, en este juego el protagonista es Zeke Holloway y podría decir de forma general que la adaptación es más libre, manteniendo como tema principal la mansión. Este juego lo jugué hace ya muchos años cuando era niño y recuerdo haber llegado hasta cierto punto y por alguna razón lo dejé y no lo volví a jugar hasta ahora. Nuestro protagonista, Zeke, deberá liberar a los espiritus ocultos en la mansión y derrotar a Aticus Thorn, regresando todo a la tranquilidad. Es un juego bastante entretenido y divertido, tiene unas buenas mecánicas que hacen del gameplay algo bastante disfrutable. El juego esta lleno de puzzles y desafíos bastante interesantes y diversos que entretienen un montón. Los enemigos no son tan diversos, sin embargo sí son algo desafiantes, pero los power ups ayudarán a enfrentarlos. El jefe final es quien me quedó debiendo un poco, pues no es un desafío tan grande como esperaría, salvo quizás el enfrentamiento final. Sin embargo y de forma general es un juego bastante divertido y entretenido, quizás desconocido para muchos, pero vale la pena probarlo. 😉

$5 entry.
*Bring your own pad/stick,please*.
3 tournament setups, 1 casual setup (PS4 version).
Prizes paid 60/30/10
.

.
- When both players are at the game console, they must come to an agreement which side of they machine they will play on (who will sit on 1p and who will sit on 2p)
.
-If an agreement cannot be reached, the TO will flip a coin that will determine who gets to pick their side.
.
- Winner must stay with the same Character, Loser may switch characters if may.
.
- Tournament will be on Default in-game settings
.
- Double Elimination Tournament .
- Random Stage Select
.
- Bring your own Controller! .

30 settembre 1988
IBM annuncia l'avvenuta spedizione di 3 milioni di personal computer PS/2.
Il PS/2 succede alle serie PC, PC/XT e PC/AT ed utilizza la Micro Channel Architecture, un formato di bus incompatibile con lo standard ISA, adottato dai costruttori di cloni.
IBM aveva presentato le sue macchine PS/2 solo l'anno prima, facendo in modo che le unità disco per floppy da 3 pollici e ½ e la VGA (Video Graphic Array) divenissero degli standard per i computer IBM ed i compatibili. I PS/2 sono stati i primi computer IBM ad utilizzare il chip 80386 di Intel ed il nuovo sistema operativo OS/2, consentendo l'utilizzo di un mouse con i computer IBM.

She is also so much fun and her abilities allow me to help push the battle forward as well as providing a space for allies to breathe.

Freeze Bomb | Horizon: Zero Dawn
.
This week, I’m showing you how to beat the heat and score some new crafting materials with this mint-and-rum cocktail that'll send a shiver down your spine.
.
@guerillagames
===
Freeze Bomb
===
1.5 oz (45ml) white rum
1 oz (30ml) pineapple rum
.25 oz (15ml) blue curacao
8-10 mint leaves
2 dashes orange bitters
.
Add the mint leaves and white rum to a mixing glass. Muddle by pressing gently with a flat tool. Strain into a shaker filled with ice. Discard mint leaves. Add the rest of the ingredients. Shake thoroughly to chill. Strain into your chosen vessel. Garnish with mint and serve!
.
See more with @sillygoosecontent
===

ComiXology Originals announces Forgotten Home. A new comic book series about magic, mystery, and family secrets. Written by Erica Schultz with Art by Marika Cresta. Featuring covers by Natasha Alterici. ⁠
⁠
SAVE this post so you can come back to the info again⁠

#Entertainment, #Comics, #Geek, #Cosplay, #VideoGames and #ComicsArt - Pontik #geeks ⁠
⁠
In Forgotten Home, Sheriff’s Deputy Lorraine Adalet investigates child disappearances all over Montana and finds a connection between many of the abductions: traces of magic! Lorraine’s search ramps up when her own teenage daughter is caught up in the kidnappings, and Lorraine learns the culprit is tied to her own past. Lorraine’s investigation leads her back to her home world of Jannada, a magical realm in a bitter war that she fled as a teenager. Now that Lorraine’s two lives have collided, she must confront her past across two worlds and save her daughter.⁠
⁠
Forgotten Home #1 is available on October 2nd⁠

This Grand Final was incredible. Haven't seen Astralis so tilted in a long time.

caption.text:
Evil Geniuses overcame Astralis to win the 4th edition of ESL One New York 🇺🇸!
The ex-NRG squad had an intense week, they decided to sign with EG just two days before the tournament started, having the pressure to demonstrate their value not only to the organization, but to the world. 
The BO5 format of the Grandfinal wasn't something they were familiar with, so many fans predicted Astralis to be the winners once again. They were clearly wrong. The NA side smashed Astralis on Inferno (16-3) followed by a convincing victory on Dust2 as well (16-12). Astralis took Train in double OT but EG finished it on Nuke (16-8) probably the best map of the Danes. 
The MVP medal was granted to Brehze, the most consistent player in the roster and I'll say very underrated too.
What do you think about EG now? Are they better than Astralis? ~ Typhon ----------------------

caption.text:
We had a jammed packed Saturday! Days like this when we go, go, go I worry how Collin is going to function in a new place.  The company Richard works for had a Carnival day for employees and their families. It was a blast! Between food trucks and carnival performers, you can't go wrong. 
As always, arriving at a new place it takes Collin a little awhile to get out of the Jeep. We typically set a timer so he knows that once the timer goes off we need to get out of the Jeep. I typically can tell when Collin is anxious about going to a new place because he will start to perseverate on something...today it was snacks. 
We did bring his Ipad just in case it was too overwhelming for him. I now have been trained to automatically pick up what will contribute to sensory overload. There were plenty... But we take it at Collin's pace and that seems to work for him. I'm pretty sure he had a good time! He loved the dunk tank and participated in dunking one of Richard's manager and the president of the company 😉 
We ended the day with a birthday party for one of Jonah's friends, Liam...friends since VPK!! The party was at a local place called The District - arcade, and bowling! All the kiddos had an amazing time!! It was nice to see Collin like every other kid, having fun playing video games...I definitely could tell after he was done playing games he was starting to have a sensory overload. He was very excited not knowing where to look or what he wanted to play...and he wanted to touch EVERYTHING! He played a handful of games and did really well, but as the evening progressed I could tell he was done. He started stimming, flapping and rocking back and forth. At that point, all the kids had burned through their game cards and it we called it a night and headed home.
.
.
.
